{
  "comment": "Per-device-type trap catalog for Juniper MX240 devices. Overlays the universal catalog (extends=true default): universal linkDown/linkUp/coldStart/warmStart/authenticationFailure carry through; Juniper-specific entries are added alongside. All entries use Class-1-only template vocabulary — entries that would want BGP/OSPF peer fields (PeerIP, PeerAS, NeighborRouterID) are explicitly deferred to a follow-up Class 2 epic. OIDs sourced from JUNIPER-MIB under jnxChassisTraps (1.3.6.1.4.1.2636.4.1); all seven are real NOTIFICATION-TYPEs registered in the MIB (verified against oidref.com and Observium's JUNIPER-MIB mirror). snmpTrapEnterprise = 1.3.6.1.4.1.2636 (Juniper Networks enterprise root) per RFC 3584 §4.1 v1↔v2c proxy convention. jnxFruEntry is indexed by 4 columns (container, L1, L2, L3), giving 4-number suffixes on varbind OIDs — not the 5-number suffixes a casual reader might infer from the visible slot/subslot encoding.",
